trans-unit.source: Exposes <see cref="T:System.Windows.UIElement3D" /> types to UI Automation.
trans-unit.target: Expone los tipos <see cref="T:System.Windows.UIElement3D" /> a la automatización de la interfaz de usuario.

trans-unit.source: By default, any class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> uses <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> to communicate with [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: De forma predeterminada, cualquier clase que herede de <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> utiliza <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> para comunicarse con [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].

trans-unit.source: If you create a class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>, you may want to provide an automation peer to support the functionality of your class.
trans-unit.target: Si crea una clase que hereda de <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>, puede que desee proporcionar una automatización del mismo nivel para admitir la funcionalidad de la clase.

trans-unit.source: Override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return a string that represents the type of the element associated with the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer>.
trans-unit.target: Invalidar el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> método para devolver una cadena que representa el tipo del elemento asociado con el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer>.

trans-unit.source: For example, if you create a class called `My3DElement` and an automation peer called `My3DElementAutomationPeer`, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return the string "My3DElement".
trans-unit.target: Por ejemplo, si crea una clase denominada `My3DElement` y llama a una automatización del mismo nivel `My3DElementAutomationPeer`, invalide el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> método para devolver la cadena "My3DElement".

trans-unit.source: If your class matches one of the known control types, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A> method to return that <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>.
trans-unit.target: Si la clase coincide con uno de los tipos de control conocidos, invalide el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A> método devuelva un valor que <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>.

trans-unit.source: Note that although the existing <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> values are generally associated with 2D controls, the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> indicates a control's functionality, not its appearance.
trans-unit.target: Tenga en cuenta que aunque existente <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> valores están generalmente asociados a controles 2D, el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> indica la funcionalidad de un control, no su apariencia.

trans-unit.source: So if your <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> invokes an action when the user clicks it, you probably want <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A> to return <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType>.
trans-unit.target: Por tanto, si su <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> invoca una acción cuando el usuario hace clic en él, probablemente desee <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A> para devolver <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType>.

trans-unit.source: The behavior of your custom <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> determines what other methods you should override.
trans-unit.target: El comportamiento de personalizado <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> determina qué otros métodos se deben invalidar.

trans-unit.source: Each method topic in the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> describes how the method is used and when it is appropriate to override it.
trans-unit.target: Cada tema de método en el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> describe cómo se utiliza el método y cuándo es adecuado invalidarlo.
